Thanks for the detailed repro! This looks like a clip propagation issue specific to the OpenGL backend — `ClipRect` on a GPU-backed canvas may not be correctly applied during `DrawPicture` playback, while the raster backend (`SKCanvasView`) handles it correctly.

As an immediate workaround, you can draw directly to the outer canvas inside the `Save`/`Restore`/`ClipRect` block without going through `SKPictureRecorder`:

```csharp
canvas.Save();
canvas.ClipRect(skr);
var matrix = SKMatrix.CreateScale(w / size, h / size);
canvas.SetMatrix(matrix);
// draw directly instead of via SKPictureRecorder
canvas.DrawPath(path, paint);
canvas.Restore();
```

We'll investigate whether this is a Skia upstream issue in the GL picture-playback clip path.
